# Files listed here are NOT synced from the template.
# See .template-docs/Help/Template-Sync.md for details.

# User application code (review CHANGELOG.md for template /web updates)
web/

# User-specific configurations
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local

# Project-specific documentation
documentation/

# Generated files
generated-docs/

# IDE settings
.vscode/
.idea/

# Don't prefix with a leading slash — actions-template-sync's ignore-file
# handler treats `/README.md` as an absolute filesystem path and errors.
# Each repo owns its own README, so we exclude it from sync.
README.md

# GitHub Actions workflow files. GitHub blocks the default GITHUB_TOKEN from
# pushing changes to .github/workflows/ files — a security policy that prevents
# a workflow from rewriting other workflows on the repo. With the current
# PAT-based sync setup the destination push uses GITHUB_TOKEN, so it cannot
# touch workflow files. We exclude the whole directory rather than fight that
# limitation; consumers update workflow files manually when needed (see
# .template-docs/Help/Template-Sync.md). This restriction will be lifted when
# sync moves to a GitHub App that can hold workflows:write.
.github/workflows/

# Template-maintainer-only files. The release channel (Digiata/Stadium-8) strips
# these via .release-ignore, but the dev-build channel (stadium-software/stadium-8)
# does not — listing them here ensures they never land in a user repo regardless
# of source, and also acts as a safety net if .release-ignore is ever incomplete.
.template-docs/CONTRIBUTING.md
.template-docs/TEMPLATE_DEVELOPMENT.md
.release-ignore
.claude/**/*.tests.js
